22 WHEREAS, the Arkansas Kids Count Coalition is a membership coalition
23 comprised of diverse individuals and organizations concerned about policies
24 impacting children in Arkansas, and is staffed by Arkansas Advocates for
25 Children and Families; and
26
27 WHEREAS, the Arkansas Kids Count Coalition serves as a strong,
28 independent nongovernmental grassroots voice for the children of Arkansas,
29 providing education and policy resources to support advocacy for the well-
30 being of all Arkansas children; and
31
32 WHEREAS, when the Arkansas Kids Count Coalition was founded in 1996,
33 one (1) in four (4) Arkansas children lived in poverty, but today those
34 figures have dropped to only one (1) in five (5); and
35
36 WHEREAS, the membership of the Arkansas Kids Count Coalition is
