5 WHEREAS, the members of the Arkansas Kids Count Coalition work to
6 improve the mental health of families, and function as nonprofits alleviating
7 hunger in their communities; and
8
9 WHEREAS, the members of the Arkansas Kids Count Coalition are retired
10 educators and parents who want to improve the lives of all the children of
11 Arkansas, no matter where those children are from or what they look like; and
12
13 WHEREAS, throughout each year, the members of the Arkansas Kids Count
14 Coalition connect with and educate advocates around Arkansas, giving them
15 tools and resources to lobby Arkansas lawmakers regarding the well-being of
16 Arkansas children; and
17
18 WHEREAS, in 2024, the Arkansas Kids Count Coalition hosted fourteen
19 (14) events in eight (8) towns in Arkansas and online, with four hundred
20 forty-two (442) total attendees; and
21
