26 WHEREAS, because of the advocacy of the members of the Arkansas Kids
27 Count Coalition, the members of the General Assembly, and Arkansas citizens
28 who lifted up the voices of children, continued progress has been seen in the
29 well-being of Arkansas children; and
30
31 WHEREAS, the Arkansas Kids Count Coalition believes that laws are made
32 by the people who show up and vows to continue to show up for Arkansas
33 children and ensure that Arkansas continues to make progress in improving the
34 lives of the children of Arkansas,
